Manual implementation takeover started on July 20, 2026.

The previous implementation worktree was created on July 19, 2026 but produced no commit or pull request. The bug is confirmed on current `dev`: `scripts/run.sh` accepts any executable `BIN` before sourcing the bootstrap contract, while the shared resolver accepts `.fkst/env`, PATH, and sibling binaries without proving their build-time substrate pin.

TDD seams:
- exact `.fkst/substrate-ref` parsing as the authoritative engine identity;
- build-time provenance probing through `fkst-framework init-package-repo` in an isolated temporary Git repository;
- explicit `BIN` and `.fkst/env` fail closed on unavailable or mismatched provenance;
- stale PATH/sibling candidates are skipped without modifying their source checkout, then pinned cache/build is used;
- matching pinned-cache and CI-injected binaries remain reusable;
- startup output exports and reports the exact source pin plus normalized `ENGINE_VER` before runtime commands execute.

> *This was generated by AI during triage.*

Implemented and merged into `dev` on July 20, 2026.

Merged commits:
- `8254b34` — enforce exact pinned FKST engine provenance before host execution;
- `1e50b69` — remove the environment listener test race discovered during full verification.

Final verification before push:
- stale sibling engine was rejected and the exact content-addressed pinned engine was selected;
- 80-run, 24-way listener stress reproducer passed 80/80;
- `environment-factory` passed 73/73 tests;
- full `./scripts/run.sh test` passed all 11 packages, repository contracts, engine provenance contracts, runner contracts, OpenSandbox tests, and the Lua coverage ratchet.

Remote `dev` now points to `1e50b69`.
